Structure : Head broader than long ( 103 : 85 ); OOC slightly smaller than IOC ( 18 : 19 ); eyes convergent ventrally, UOD:LOD ( 67 : 47 ); clypeus broader than long ( 34 : 26 ); labrum with concave dorsal margin; vertex slightly concave in frontal view behind ocellar triangle; weak, median, longitudinal groove on basal half of clypeus, ratio of lengths of pedicel:F 1 -F 3 — 15 : 16 : 21 : 22 (ratio of pedicel to F 1 variable, always less than 1 ); gena less than half as wide as the eye in lateral view ( 13 : 33 ); ratio of lengths of mesoscutum: scutellum: metanotum: dorsal area of propodeum — 81 : 31 : 15 : 25 ; hind femur maximum length to maximum depth — 91 : 40 ; hind tibia highly modified (
Fig. 1 E, F
), length: width: depth — 68 : 23 : 25 ; anteroventral surface widely expanded, anteroventral margin convex except distinctly concave just before apex; deep, preapical concavity basal to transverse apical lamina; ratio of lengths of hind tibia and hind basitarsus — 55 : 39 ; S 1 apex with ventrally oriented, apically concave process; S 7 ventral lobes broad with apical concavity, dorsal lobes elongate and clavate (
